28// static
29std::unique_ptr<ChannelManager> ChannelManager::Create(
30 std::unique_ptr<MediaEngineInterface> media_engine,
31 bool enable_rtx,
32 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
33 rtc::Thread* network_thread) {
34 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread);
35 RTC_DCHECK(network_thread);
36 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread);
37
38 if (media_engine)
39 media_engine->Init();
40
41 return absl::WrapUnique(new ChannelManager(
42 std::move(media_engine), enable_rtx, worker_thread, network_thread));
43}
44
45ChannelManager::ChannelManager(
46 std::unique_ptr<MediaEngineInterface> media_engine,
47 bool enable_rtx,
48 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
49 rtc::Thread* network_thread)
50 : media_engine_(std::move(media_engine)),
51 worker_thread_(worker_thread),
52 network_thread_(network_thread),
53 enable_rtx_(enable_rtx) {
54 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_);
55 RTC_DCHECK(network_thread_);
56 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
57}
58
59ChannelManager::~ChannelManager() {
60 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
61}

63void ChannelManager::GetSupportedAudioSendCodecs(
64 std::vector<AudioCodec>* codecs) const {
65 if (!media_engine_) {
66 return;
67 }
68 *codecs = media_engine_->voice().send_codecs();
69}
70
71void ChannelManager::GetSupportedAudioReceiveCodecs(
72 std::vector<AudioCodec>* codecs) const {
73 if (!media_engine_) {
74 return;
75 }
76 *codecs = media_engine_->voice().recv_codecs();
77}
78
79void ChannelManager::GetSupportedVideoSendCodecs(
80 std::vector<VideoCodec>* codecs) const {
81 if (!media_engine_) {
82 return;
83 }
84 codecs->clear();
85
86 std::vector<VideoCodec> video_codecs = media_engine_->video().send_codecs();
87 for (const auto& video_codec : video_codecs) {
88 if (!enable_rtx_ &&
89 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(kRtxCodecName, video_codec.name)) {
90 continue;
91 }
92 codecs->push_back(video_codec);
93 }
94}
95
96void ChannelManager::GetSupportedVideoReceiveCodecs(
97 std::vector<VideoCodec>* codecs) const {
98 if (!media_engine_) {
99 return;
100 }
101 codecs->clear();
102
103 std::vector<VideoCodec> video_codecs = media_engine_->video().recv_codecs();
104 for (const auto& video_codec : video_codecs) {
105 if (!enable_rtx_ &&
106 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(kRtxCodecName, video_codec.name)) {
107 continue;
108 }
109 codecs->push_back(video_codec);
110 }
111}

141VoiceChannel* ChannelManager::CreateVoiceChannel(
142 webrtc::Call* call,
143 const MediaConfig& media_config,
144 webrtc::RtpTransportInternal* rtp_transport,
145 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
146 const std::string& content_name,
147 bool srtp_required,
148 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
149 rtc::UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
150 const AudioOptions& options) {
151 RTC_DCHECK(call);
152 RTC_DCHECK(media_engine_);
153 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11992): Remove this workaround after updates in
154 // PeerConnection and add the expectation that we're already on the right
155 // thread.
156 if (!worker_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
157 return worker_thread_->Invoke<VoiceChannel*>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
158 return CreateVoiceChannel(call, media_config, rtp_transport,
159 signaling_thread, content_name, srtp_required,
160 crypto_options, ssrc_generator, options);
161 });
162 }
163
164 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
165
166 VoiceMediaChannel* media_channel = media_engine_->voice().CreateMediaChannel(
167 call, media_config, options, crypto_options);
168 if (!media_channel) {
169 return nullptr;
170 }
171
172 auto voice_channel = std::make_unique<VoiceChannel>(
173 worker_thread_, network_thread_, signaling_thread,
174 absl::WrapUnique(media_channel), content_name, srtp_required,
175 crypto_options, ssrc_generator);
176
177 voice_channel->Init_w(rtp_transport);
178
179 VoiceChannel* voice_channel_ptr = voice_channel.get();
180 voice_channels_.push_back(std::move(voice_channel));
181 return voice_channel_ptr;
182}
183
184void ChannelManager::DestroyVoiceChannel(VoiceChannel* voice_channel) {
185 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "ChannelManager::DestroyVoiceChannel");
186 RTC_DCHECK(voice_channel);
187
188 if (!worker_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
189 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE,
190 [&] { DestroyVoiceChannel(voice_channel); });
191 return;
192 }
193
194 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
195
196 voice_channels_.erase(absl::c_find_if(
197 voice_channels_, [&](const std::unique_ptr<VoiceChannel>& p) {
198 return p.get() == voice_channel;
199 }));
200}

202VideoChannel* ChannelManager::CreateVideoChannel(
203 webrtc::Call* call,
204 const MediaConfig& media_config,
205 webrtc::RtpTransportInternal* rtp_transport,
206 rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
207 const std::string& content_name,
208 bool srtp_required,
209 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
210 rtc::UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
211 const VideoOptions& options,
212 webrtc::VideoBitrateAllocatorFactory* video_bitrate_allocator_factory) {
213 RTC_DCHECK(call);
214 RTC_DCHECK(media_engine_);
215 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11992): Remove this workaround after updates in
216 // PeerConnection and add the expectation that we're already on the right
217 // thread.
218 if (!worker_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
219 return worker_thread_->Invoke<VideoChannel*>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
220 return CreateVideoChannel(call, media_config, rtp_transport,
221 signaling_thread, content_name, srtp_required,
222 crypto_options, ssrc_generator, options,
223 video_bitrate_allocator_factory);
224 });
225 }
226
227 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
228
229 VideoMediaChannel* media_channel = media_engine_->video().CreateMediaChannel(
230 call, media_config, options, crypto_options,
231 video_bitrate_allocator_factory);
232 if (!media_channel) {
233 return nullptr;
234 }
235
236 auto video_channel = std::make_unique<VideoChannel>(
237 worker_thread_, network_thread_, signaling_thread,
238 absl::WrapUnique(media_channel), content_name, srtp_required,
239 crypto_options, ssrc_generator);
240
241 video_channel->Init_w(rtp_transport);
242
243 VideoChannel* video_channel_ptr = video_channel.get();
244 video_channels_.push_back(std::move(video_channel));
245 return video_channel_ptr;
246}
247
248void ChannelManager::DestroyVideoChannel(VideoChannel* video_channel) {
249 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "ChannelManager::DestroyVideoChannel");
250 RTC_DCHECK(video_channel);
251
252 if (!worker_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
253 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE,
254 [&] { DestroyVideoChannel(video_channel); });
255 return;
256 }
257 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
258
259 video_channels_.erase(absl::c_find_if(
260 video_channels_, [&](const std::unique_ptr<VideoChannel>& p) {
261 return p.get() == video_channel;
262 }));
263}

265bool ChannelManager::StartAecDump(webrtc::FileWrapper file,
266 int64_t max_size_bytes) {
267 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
268 return media_engine_->voice().StartAecDump(std::move(file), max_size_bytes);
269}
270
271void ChannelManager::StopAecDump() {
272 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
273 media_engine_->voice().StopAecDump();
274}
